cl-sdl (0.2.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * The ``Accumulated bugfixes of 10 months'' release.
    - Ignas Mikalajunas found a ``memory leak'' in the foreign interface.
    - Julian Stecklina sent a patch to support FreeBSD
    - Nikodemus Siivola points out that cl-sdl depends on libsdl1.2-dev too
      (Closes: #188059).
      + Also added appropriate -dev deps to ttf/mix/img.
    - Dan Knapp had a clever patch to speed-up foreign struct access in cmucl.
    - David Morse had trouble installing cl-sdl-opengl without glu dev libs.
    - Apologies if I've left you out of this list, that's all I have.
  * New functions: get-pixel and get-rgb.
  * Miscellaneous clean-ups, etc.
  * Build Arch: all packages in binary-indep (Closes: #174385).
  * Now using libsdl-ttf2.0.
  * Updated Standards Version to 3.6.1.
  * Changing maintainer address.
  * Joystick support patch from Dick Gerrits.

 -- Matthew Danish <mrd@debian.org>  Mon,  3 Nov 2003 12:30:40 -0500

cl-sdl (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New foreign library loading framework
    - more flexible, less hassle
    - better at finding libraries
    - understands dependencies
  * Improvements to search paths
  * MinGW support
  * Eliminated need for sdlmixstub, for now
  * Minor bugfixes

 -- Matthew Danish <mdanish@andrew.cmu.edu>  Wed,  1 Jan 2003 14:02:35 -0500

cl-sdl (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Lots of new SDL, SDL-TTF, SDL-IMG, SDL-MIX functionality.
  * CL-SDL, CL-SDL-TTF packages with Lispier interface.
  * Various bugfixes.

 -- Matthew Danish <mdanish@andrew.cmu.edu>  Wed, 18 Dec 2002 20:14:03 -0500

